snippet.textDisplay: Thank you Doctor Mike, for not making this video about how much more dangerous the flu is and how everyone's anxiety is overly dramatic as I've been told by other healthcare professionals. Although flu has a high death toll, there's so much research on it, controlled studies, a vaccine available and certain precautions people can take. This new strain of corona virus has particularly claimed 361 victims to this day and only started on the 16th of December. I just recently had a "feud" with one of my doctor colleagues telling me I'm "bloody dramatic" about it and how it's not nearly as bad as flu, however the truth is there is SO MUCH we don't know and claims like that telling people they shouldn't worry at all "because more people die from flu" are quite irresponsible in my opinion. Thanks again for being educational and leaving room for the unknown because people tend to make claims left and right, including medical professionals, that could potentially turn out to be far from the truth.
